The paper discusses the development of a framework for interactive information retrieval (IIR) evaluation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and human-computer interaction (HCI). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.HC are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of logging and mapping components, which are related to data management and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the analysis of search behavior, which can involve natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques (cs.CL and cs.DL).
